The characteristics of the PV module depend on the cell temperature, the sun radiation level, and so on. Some of these factors, such as the temperature and the irradiation, change may be made continuously throughout the day, and as a result, the characteristics of the cell change. We should briefly examine these factors [17]:
Temperature: an increase in temperature decreases the voltage and the current that is almost constant as shown in Fig.Â 3.Fig.Â 3
Changes of the PV array curves or temperature at constant radiation intensity
The intensity of the sun radiation: the increase in the intensity of the radiation increases the current and the voltage that is almost constant as shown in Fig.Â 4.Fig.Â 4
Changes of the PV array curves or the radiation intensity at constant temperature
